episodes.title: Ikari Bakuhatsu: Ore ga Zenbu Hikiukeru
episodes.plot: Cavendish shows up just in time to stop Doflamingo's attack from hitting Robin, allowing Luffy to focus on fighting Doflamingo as Cavendish flees the plateau with everybody.

episodes.title: Gear Fourth! Kyoui no Bounce Man!
episodes.plot: Luffy casts off his sandals and activates Gear Fourth. His body changes with a ballooned torso covered with tribal like markings and coated with Busoshoku Haki.

episodes.title: Daigyakushuu! Doflamingo no Kakusei!
episodes.plot: Zoro and others head off to stop the Birdcage as Luffy continues battling Doflamingo. However, he reveals that his Devil Fruit has awakened, and he overwhelms Luffy by turning the surrounding area into string.

episodes.title: Luffy! Konshin no Leo Bazooka
episodes.plot: Luffy uses up too much Haki causing Gear Forth to end before dealing the final blow. Meanwhile, the citizens of Dressrosa run away from the shrinking Birdcage in hopes of protecting their lives.

episodes.title: Kaen Ryuuou: Luffy no Inochi o Mamorinuke
episodes.plot: Luffy runs out of Haki. Gyats of the Colosseum helps him to get way from Doflamigo for 10 minutes so that he can regain Haki.

episodes.title: Kiseki no Namida: Mansherry no Tatakai!
episodes.plot: All the gladiators from the Colosseum get recovered by Mansherry's healing ability and they start stopping the bird cage along with Zoro and the others which has fastened up.

episodes.title: Inochi no Kagiri: Shi no Tori Kago o Tomero!
episodes.plot: The Marines and citizens on Dressrosa take part in the effort to halt the Birdcage, and briefly manage to bring it to a standstill.

episodes.title: Sei ka Shi ka: Unmei no Countdown
episodes.plot: Luffy regains his Haki and appears before Doflamingo.

episodes.title: Ten o Utsu: Luffy Ikari no King Kong Gun
episodes.plot: In order to defeat Doflamingo with a single blow, Luffy unleashes all his power in a punch... The King Kong Gun.

episodes.title: Jiyuu e! Yorokobi no Dressrosa!
episodes.plot: Luffy finally defeated the evil Doflamingo, and the kingdom of Dressrosa is overfilled with joy!

episodes.title: Zendaimimon: Taishou Fujitora Shougeki no Ketsudan!
episodes.plot: Admiral Fujitora apologizes and confesses to King Riku about the seven warlord system in front of the video transponder snail, hence being witnessed by 3 nearby countries.

episodes.title: Gekishin Hashiru: Ugokidasu Saiaku no Sedai!
episodes.plot: Doflamingo's defeat spreads across the world. Worst generation and it's plans get revealed. Due to Fujitora's confession to King Riku and the exact truth spreading all over the world, Navy and the Government are disappointed with Fujitora.

episodes.title: Densetsu Tanjou: Kakumei Senshi Sabo no Bouken!
episodes.plot: Sabo's past after the incident with the celestial dragon is told to the straw hats and group at Kyros' home. Meanwhile, the whole city is being reconstructed.

episodes.title: Kyoudai no Kizuna: Luffy Sabo Saikai Hiwa
episodes.plot: Sabo remembers his past.

episodes.title: Saikyou no Seibutsu: Yonkou - Hyakujuu no Kaidou
episodes.plot: Suicidal maniac emperor shows himself up. Sanji and the others are in Zou.

episodes.title: Fujitora Ugoku: Mugiwara no Ichimi Kanzen Houimou
episodes.plot: Fujitora makes his decision to chase the Straw Hat alliance meanwhile Kyros makes his decision not to meet his daughter for some reasons.

episodes.title: Hijoujitai: Sarawareta Rebecca!
episodes.plot: The Marines swarm Kyros' house, and the Straw Hats, Law, Bartolomeo, and Bellamy escape from it. However, Luffy departs from the group, saying he needed to do something. Marines occupy the entirety of Dressrosa, but the Corrida Colosseum gladiators take them out in order to clear the way for the Straw Hats.

episodes.title: Oyako no Kizuna: Kyros to Rebecca!
episodes.plot: Rebecca has precious little time to follow Luffy's lead and make it to Kyros. Can she make it in time? Meanwhile, Fujitora is closing in on Bartolomeo and the other Colosseum warriors while Trafalgar Law faces the shadows of his past.

episodes.title: Otoko no Iji: Luffy tai Fujitora Makkou Shoubu
episodes.plot: Luffy and Fujitora face head-on. Luffy shows sympathy towards Fujitora which angers the latter

episodes.title: Nigeba Nashi: Taishou Fujitora Hijou no Tsuigeki!
episodes.plot: The Straw Hats, samurai, and Corrida Colosseum gladiators escape from Admiral Fujitora and run to their ships. Fujitora prepares to crush them with his floating rubble, but the citizens of Dressrosa chase after the criminals with the apparent intention of taking down the Straw Hats themselves due to Luffy kidnapping Rebecca. However, they really knew where Rebecca is and are doing this as a ruse to prevent Fujitora from dropping the rubble and help the Straw Hats escape.

episodes.title: Kobun no Sakazuki: Kessei! Mugiwara Daisendan!
episodes.plot: Luffy refuses his allies' request to serve under him. But everyone pledge their allegiance anyway. They come under attack but Fujitora helps. The Grand Fleet celebrates their formation. It's hinted they will play a vital role in future.

episodes.title: Gun'yuukakyo: Arekuruu Shinsekai no Kaibutsu-tachi
episodes.plot: CP-0 agents Rob Lucci and Spandam search Dressrosa for weapons, but find none. The people of Dressrosa celebrate a new era in their history, as the existence of the dwarves is revealed to the humans and they begin fully coexisting, and Riku Doldo III prepares for Levely. Out at sea, an imprisoned Donquixote Doflamingo wonders who will gain power over the entire world. Meanwhile, the pirate Jack prepares to attack the Marine convoy transporting Doflamingo.

episodes.title: Gin no Yousai: Luffy to Barto Daibouken
episodes.plot: While heading to the next island, Zou, Luffy's appetite causes them trouble and he and Bartolomeo find themselves entangled in the scheme of a pirate lord who can manipulate silver.

episodes.title: Chika Meikyuu: Luffy tai Torokko Ningen
episodes.plot: The Tram-Man arrives. And has Luffy, Bartolomeo and Desire on the run. The deeper the three fall into the pit, however, the more clear it becomes that Bill's group hides a terrible secret.

episodes.title: Kengi Hakunetsu: Law Zoro Tsui ni Kenzan!
episodes.plot: Zoro and the rest of the group arrive to help Luffy.

episodes.title: Zettaizetsumei: Luffy Kyokugen no Shakunetsu Kessen
episodes.plot: Luffy, Desire, and Bartolomeo go up against Bill. But the mad, Smelt-Smelt man becomes deranged and lets his true power unfurl. Do Luffy and the others have any hope of exposing Bill's self-serving aims and turning his gang against him?

episodes.title: Bouken Kaimaku: Maboroshi no Shima "Zou" Touchaku!
episodes.plot: Bartolomeo tells his crew about how the Straw Hats met. The crew arrives at Zou.

episodes.title: Shin Shichi Bukai: Densetsu Shirohige no Musuko Toujou
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Kesshi no Tozou: Kyozou no Se no Daibouken!
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Sentou Kaishi: Luffy vs Mink-zoku!
episodes.plot: Luffy pushes deeper into the mysterious forest on the elephant's back, but he's treading in territory where is not welcome. Meanwhile, Usopp and the others make a startling discovery in a ruined city.

episodes.title: Garchuu! Mugiwara no Ichimi Saishuuketsu
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Hangeki Kaishi: Guruwara no Ichimi Daikatsuyaku!
episodes.plot: Luffy and the others are unexpectedly welcomed at the fortress and treated well by the Minks, although they have to navigate some cultural differences - And Nami starts sharing what happened to them after they left Dressrosa.

episodes.title: Kyoui Shuurai: Hyakujuu Kaizokudan Jack!
episodes.plot: Luffy and the others learn about the dangerous intruders who have come to Zou, and why the island is wrecked. Afterwards, Luffy's loose lips get them into trouble.

episodes.title: Hiru no Ou: Inuarashi Koushaku Toujou!
episodes.plot: Duke Dogstorm - the Straw Hats finally meet the ruler of this strange land, and learn more about the battle that took place here; and the mysterious system by which the island is ruled.

episodes.title: Yoru no Ou: Nekomamushi no Danna Kenzan
episodes.plot: Day turns to night as the Minks keep up their onslaught against the invading Beast Pirates. But Jack's amazing Devil Fruit power may end the elephant island once and for all.

episodes.title: Shuto Kaimetsu: Guruware no Ichimi Jouriku!
episodes.plot: Night and day, Jack faces the fury of the two sworn defenders of Zou, but while they put up a good fight, the Minks aren't able to subdue Jack, especially after he brings out his secret weapon.

episodes.title: Limit Semaru: Mink-zoku to Ichimi no Kizuna!
episodes.plot: In the aftermath of Jack's deadly attack on the island of Zou, Chopper and Sanji rush in to save the fallen Mink Tribe - but they will need the help of Caesar to overcome the poisonous effects of the gas.

episodes.title: Akudou Kikyou: Yonkou Big Mom no Shikaku
episodes.plot: Big Mom's crew comes to Zou.

episodes.title: Shissou no Shinjitsu: Sanji Kyougaku no Shoutaijou
episodes.plot: The mystery of Sanji's disappearance deepens as Luffy learns that Big Mom's lackeys have caught up with him and the rest - and carry with them an invitation from Big Mom that simply can't be refused.

episodes.title: Yarou Domo e: Sanji Wakare no Okitegami
episodes.plot: Sanji's dire situation has become clear but instead of rallying against Big Mom's crew, he submits to go along with them to bring an end to this situation. But being separated from one of his crew is more than Luffy is willing to tolerate.

episodes.title: Nekomamushi no Danna ni Ai ni Ikou
episodes.plot: There's only one key to finding out what happened to Sanji - and Luffy and the others make their way towards finding out more about their friend's disappearance, but on their way the indigenous fauna give them trouble.

episodes.title: Luffy Ketsudan: Sanji Dattai no Kiki!
episodes.plot: Luffy hatches a plan to help Sanji, but he'll have to go alone to avoid an all-out war with Big Mom. Meanwhile, Kin'emon and Kanjuro finally arrive at Zou, unwittingly setting the stage for the Minks' thirst for revenge.

episodes.title: Isshokusokuhatsu: Inu to Neko to Samurai!
episodes.plot: News about Kin'emon and Kanjuro's arrival is spread around the "Zou", panic has started. Meanwhile Straw hat's members are trying to hide them, but Kin'emon manages to show up and unexpected event's taking place.

episodes.title: Sanninme! Ninja Kiri no Raizou Toujou
episodes.plot: The Ninja for whom everyone were prepared to give their life for, comes to light. But will he meet the crews expectations?

episodes.title: Akai Ishi! "One Piece" e no Michishirube
episodes.plot: The mysteries of ninjutsu enthrall the Straw Hats as Raizo, the implausible ninja, makes his true powers known. Meanwhile, a mysterious artifact points the way towards the end of the Grand Line.

episodes.title: Wano Kuni no Himitsu: Kouzuki-ke to Rekishi no Ponegliffs
episodes.plot: The mystery of the Ponegliffs is revealed - their true significance, and the story of their creation, leads closer to the Straw Hats than they might have imagined.
